title: For Sale:  Springfield 1911 9mm w/ LOTS of extras
postcontent:
ADDED STOCK PHOTO W/ SIMILAR GRIPS.  I have original crossed cannon grips as well as better quality VX G-10 grips with blackened screws.

This is the nicest pistol I've ever owned. Trigger breaks like glass and it is a tackdriver. Hate to put it up for sale, but it is too big for me to CCW comfortably and it isn't getting shot at the range. Since I bought this nearly 2 years ago I fired it at the range once, cleaned it, and put it in the safe. Every now and then I took it out to fondle but that's about it. Was carrying a Star BM instead but decided that was too heavy for me as well. I've decided to move away from this caliber altogether.

I have a lightly used Springfield Armory Stainless Loaded 9mm with adjustable sights & ambi safety in the original blue plastic case with papers and all the stuff that came with it, including a Kydex holster and dual mag carrier. Info on this piece is at their website here: http://www.springfield-armory.com/armory.php?version=22

Pistol's prior owner had a great gunsmith lighten the trigger to about 3#. It is the best trigger job I've ever seen. He stated he only put a few hundred rounds through it before deciding he wanted a .45 instead. I put less than 50 rds through it myself. There are a few minor scuffs on the stainless finish that were there when I bought it -- looks like from the original owner drawing it from the Kydex. I have the original grips but replaced them with VZ Double Diamond in black G-10 which looks nicer and feels great. http://vzgrips.com/gun-grips/1911-pistol-grips-1/double-diamonds-1/double-diamond-black-g10 Aside from that, the only change I made to this piece was to touch up the sights with a bit of nail polish (white on the back, red on the front) which I think is an improvement, but if you don't like it or want to redo it, it is very easily removed with a bit of acetone on a swab.

In addition to the aforementioned Kydex holster (RH), I have several other holsters that I could include, first two I'll throw in for free, willing to work out a deal on the other two. One is a cheapo ambi belt slide that I got for free and never used, the others are really nice. First one is a Galco IWB tuckable w/J-hook (LH). Next is an impossible to find Israeli Front Line IWB with teflon lining (LH). Last is a Galco Miami Classic shoulder rig in like new condition. This is set up for LH, but you can make it RH simply by switching it around, but if you want to get a proper RH holster for a clean draw Optics Planet has one you can add on for about $40 (this is a modular system).

I have a total of 7 top quality magazines for this pistol. This takes 9rd mags but one is a Wilson 10rd.

I have well over a grand in this package.

I'm asking $850 cash for everything.


Would do an even exchange for an EMP.

For partial trades, I like .25 automatics. Might consider .380 but I'm picky. I like the SIG P230 and the chrome slide LCP.  No more long guns -- I haven't got any room for them.

I am in no hurry to sell. I will likely regret selling this. But it is impractical for me because my eyes aren't good enough to target shoot and it is too big for me to carry. Someone wants this. Open to reasonable offers but please do not insult me with ridiculous lowballs.

I will try to get pics up tomorrow night. Trust me, it is really nice. Like new except for light holster wear.

WILL NOT SHIP

NO BAD GUYS

Thanks.
